<h3 id="toc29"><span>== PAGE COMMENTARY &#8212; ARCHIVED ==</span></h3>
<h5 id="toc30"><span>Last updated: June 2018.</span></h5>
<hr />
<p><strong>Floppy Says:</strong> This commentary covers only one-fifth of my written work on the Wiki. I won't update this again, if only because there's too much work to make commentary on, and I would rather let my work speak for itself.</p>
<p>If you're curious, I do include some writing/background information in the author posts for all my individual works.</p>
<hr />
<h3 id="toc31"><span><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">SCP-2641: Before the Fire</span> <strong>[DELETED]</strong></span></h3>
<h3 id="toc32"><span>URA-2641 and <a href="/solidao">Solidão</a></span></h3>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;▷&nbsp;Learn&nbsp;more?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Summary:</strong> SCP-2641 was an ancient sapient concept that lived inside literary media.</p>
<p>Persons exposed to affected media became a physical conduit connecting 2641 with the outside world. 2641 made objects act tangentially to the way they're meant to, and in a surreal manner. Each time, it spread into a new medium; each time, it gained power. After 2641 connected with enough objects, media, and people, it regained its lost reality-bending properties.</p>
<p>This SCP featured:</p>
<ul>
<li>A dense rainforest.</li>
<li>A mysterious cult contained by the Brazilian government.</li>
<li>Exploding spears.</li>
<li>A father wishing to save his daughter.</li>
<li>An exiled and disillusioned denizen from Plato's World of Forms.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p><strong>Commentary:</strong> SCP-2641 was my 1st SCP, written in April 2017 after the SCP-3000 &quot;Horror&quot; Contest.</p>
<p>2641 was an experiment. I wanted to write an SCP that was contained within its own documentation. I wanted to justify why the Foundation would even do such a thing. And I wanted to show that there was something very wrong happening behind the scenes. I wasn't the most successful in executing these three things, but at the time, I was happy with how everything turned out.</p>
<p>The idea began with, &quot;what if objects acted the <em>opposite</em> of how they're supposed to?&quot; It took a lot of writing and rewriting to make that idea make sense.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Themes:</strong> Brazilian governmental politics; isolation; revenge.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>UPDATE:</strong> I self-deleted this page in mid-2018. I was unhappy with its performance over its lifetime on the site (just over a year), and I didn't think I was a good enough author to execute it yet.</p>
<p>Though the concept had been dropped, I still consider its existence a part of my Authorial Canon.</p>
<p>If you still wish to read this story, it exists in a different format without all the filler:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/solidao">Solidão</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">△&nbsp;Close</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<h3 id="toc33"><span><a href="/scp-3787">SCP-3787: The Horse Meme</a></span></h3>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;▷&nbsp;Learn&nbsp;more?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Summary:</strong> A mysterious group of antimemetic equine entities is trying to give themselves some power on Earth. To counteract this, in what is perhaps the failed <em>Deus ex Machina</em> of a drowsy god, horses begin breeding 10 times more quickly. The size of equine concepts in the collective human headspace increases dramatically, and humans become very afraid. This increase in &quot;conceptual horseness&quot;, however, is effective in scaring away the entities &#8212; who fear the more powerful common Horse.</p>
<p>Of course, the Foundation tries to contain this strange horse anomaly by slowing down horse birth rates. Not only do they start a mass horse die-off, but the entities pour into our world to wreak havoc throughout North America.</p>
<p>This page has many things packed into it &#8212; such as an explanation for where modern-day mnestics come from, and the SCP-2000 of horses. It also features Mobile Task Force Pi-5 (&quot;Glue Factory&quot;), which battles antimemetic horse people with laser weapons, and is frankly <em>the coolest gosh darn thing ever.</em></p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Commentary:</strong> SCP-3787 was my 2nd SCP, written in February 2018.</p>
<p>It took an awfully long time to come up with a second SCP. 3787 was far more ambitious than 2641, and I pitched it by referring to it as &quot;the 001 of horse anomalies&quot;. Like with 2641, I was unhappy with the way I executed things. This time, however, I later went back and cleaned it up.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Themes:</strong> The dangers of creeping nationalism; nyctophobia; the Foundation at war.</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">△&nbsp;Close</a></div>
</div>
