<h3 id="toc34"><span><a href="/scp-3719">SCP-3719: Your Friendly Neighbourhood Lawnmower</a></span></h3>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;▷&nbsp;Learn&nbsp;more?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Summary:</strong> It's a lawnmower. Somehow, it ended up in a Baltimore suburb, quickly making the neighbourhood closer than it's ever been &#8212; by fusing a bunch of residents into a 5,000-kg flesh ball that mows lawns perpetually. <em>And they enjoy it.</em></p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Commentary:</strong> SCP-3719 was my 3rd SCP, written in March 2018.</p>
<p>I haven't much to talk about in terms of how I wrote it because, to be honest, only a few days passed between when I started and when I posted. I wanted to write something like this for about a year before I actually posted it, but couldn't figure out how.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Themes:</strong> Tragedies in the news; body horror; community bonds.</p>
