<h3 id="toc36"><span><a href="/scp-3464">SCP-3464: Olive Garden regularly communes with DEMONIC ENTITIES to summon their SATANIC sempiternal garlic bread</a></span></h3>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;▷&nbsp;Learn&nbsp;more?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Summary:</strong> Some wizardy assholes steal Mr. Krab's secret garlic bread formula and start summoning demons with it.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Commentary:</strong> SCP-3464 was my 5th SCP, written in May 2018.</p>
<p>Five years ago, I wrote an extremely gross creepypasta about an ever-growing garlic bread, and a person who had to eat their way through it. The strange shenanigans involved with such a phenomenon were my inspiration here. So, the plan was to make it a relatively inane anart project used to spread the word about food waste. That's a pretty important thing, but it's probably at the <em>bottom</em> of the Foundation's list of things to worry about when the universe could spontaneously turn into cheese.</p>
<p>What other aspects are at place? There's the ghostly voice of Don LaFontaine; a Foundation thaumaturge (because they have those too); demonic shenanigans inspired heavily by Third Law; and an actual demon possessing a hunk of garlic bread.</p>
<p>This one's a fun romp altogether &#8212; I promise!</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Themes:</strong> Sabotage; demons; wizard chefs.</p>
</div>
