<h3 id="toc62"><span>== WRITING/INSPIRATION/COMMUNITY ==</span></h3>
<h5 id="toc63"><span>&quot;Inspiration&quot;, &quot;Themes&quot;, and &quot;Miscellaneous Thoughts&quot; are mostly outdated.</span></h5>
<hr />
<p><strong>Inspiration:</strong> I'm greatly inspired by science fiction, and I'm a big fan of the <em>Halo</em> series. My stories are typically science fiction/science fantasy-oriented (specifically featuring magical technology), and I always like taking some wacky concept and exploring it to its logical extreme. I'm not always the most successful, but I do try!</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Themes:</strong> I like writing about community, family, and camaraderie. When writing an SCP, I typically think of the object or concept first and slowly inject related concepts into the mix. When I've figured that out, I try telling an emotional story about that object or concept. My favourite things to write are the conceptual and the metafictional.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Miscellaneous Thoughts:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>My favourite SCP is <a href="/scp-2747">SCP-2747</a></li>
<li>Much of my work is set in Site-82.</li>
<li>I would <em>love</em> to write a time travel SCP some day.</li>
<li>My goals are to read every site Canon, improve my character writing, and write a lot more in general.</li>
</ul>
